name: r-inext
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = '2.0.20' %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-inext
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/iNEXT_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/iNEXT/iNEXT_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 4fb32f985d9491d465d3f13026b5619e1ef94457429107e228722809967e6a91

build:
  merge_build_host: True  # [win]
  number: 1
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-ggplot2
    - r-reshape2
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-ggplot2
    - r-reshape2

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('iNEXT')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('iNEXT')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: http://chao.stat.nthu.edu.tw/wordpress/software_download/
  license: GPL-3.0-or-later
  summary: 'Provides simple functions to compute and plot two types (sample-size- and coverage-based)
    rarefaction and extrapolation of species diversity (Hill numbers) for individual-based
    (abundance) data or sampling-unit- based (incidence) data. (Hsieh, Ma and Chao 2014)
    <doi: 10.1111/2041-210X.12613>.'
  license_family: GPL3
  license_file:
    - '{{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-3'

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
    - brendanf

# Package: iNEXT
# Type: Package
# Title: Interpolation and Extrapolation for Species Diversity
# Version: 2.0.20
# Author: T. C. Hsieh, K. H. Ma and Anne Chao
# Description: Provides simple functions to compute and plot two types (sample-size- and coverage-based) rarefaction and extrapolation of species diversity (Hill numbers) for individual-based (abundance) data or sampling-unit- based (incidence) data. (Hsieh, Ma and Chao 2014) <doi: 10.1111/2041-210X.12613>.
